Quayle alluded to the National Guard issue during his speech, saying he was proud of the six years he served. A Bush aide said the matter was discussed with the Indiana senator during the process that led to his selection for the Bush ticket, and Quayle had denied that he used influence to gain admittance to the Guard.  Phillippi _ who worked for Quayle's grandfather, Eugene C.  Gen. Bush, who followed his running mate to the podium, said he was proud to have Dan Quayle at my side. 